---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About the Breed | Dapper Doxie"
  description="Learn about Dachshund temperament, size, coat types, health considerations, and whether the breed is the right fit for your home."
  keywords="Dachshund breed information, mini dachshund temperament, standard dachshund personality, dachshund care"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="About the Breed"
    subtitle="Everything you should know before welcoming a Dachshund into your home"
    breadcrumbs={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'About the Breed' }
    ]}
  />

  <section class="breed-page">
    <div class="breed-container">
      <article class="intro-card">
        <h2>Dachshunds: Small Dogs with Big Hearts</h2>
        <p>
          Dachshunds are known for their loyal personalities, playful energy, and unique long-bodied build.
          At Dapper Doxie, we raise our puppies in a family setting so they are confident, social, and
          ready for real home life. Whether you are choosing a Miniature or Standard Dachshund, you can
          expect a loving companion who bonds deeply with their people.
        </p>
      </article>

      <section class="traits-grid">
        <article class="trait-card">
          <h3>Temperament</h3>
          <p>Affectionate, alert, and people-focused. Dachshunds love being close to their family and thrive on daily interaction.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="trait-card">
          <h3>Energy Level</h3>
          <p>Moderate. They enjoy playtime and short walks, then happily settle in for cuddles and rest.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="trait-card">
          <h3>Trainability</h3>
          <p>Smart and responsive with consistency. Positive reinforcement and short sessions work best.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="trait-card">
          <h3>Family Fit</h3>
          <p>Excellent with respectful children and adults. Early socialization helps build confidence in new settings.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="info-card">
        <h2>Size and Coat Overview</h2>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Variety</th>
                <th>Typical Adult Weight</th>
                <th>Coat & Grooming</th>
                <th>Personality Style</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Miniature Smooth</td>
                <td>8-11 lbs</td>
                <td>Short coat, low maintenance, weekly brushing</td>
                <td>Bold, curious, lively</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Miniature Longhair</td>
                <td>8-11 lbs</td>
                <td>Silky coat, brush 3-4 times per week</td>
                <td>Gentle, affectionate, calm</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Standard Smooth</td>
                <td>16-32 lbs</td>
                <td>Short coat, easy upkeep</td>
                <td>Confident, loyal, sturdy</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="info-card">
        <h2>Health and Lifestyle Considerations</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Keep your Dachshund at a healthy weight to reduce stress on the spine and joints.</li>
          <li>Use ramps for furniture when possible and avoid frequent jumping from high surfaces.</li>
          <li>Provide daily exercise and mental stimulation with toys, scent games, and training.</li>
          <li>Schedule regular veterinary care and stay current on vaccines, parasite prevention, and dental care.</li>
          <li>Choose a secure harness over neck-only pressure for routine walks.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="info-card">
        <h2>Is a Dachshund Right for You?</h2>
        <p>Dachshunds are a great fit if you are looking for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A loyal companion who wants to be part of your daily routine.</li>
          <li>A small-to-medium dog with personality and confidence.</li>
          <li>A breed that does well in both apartments and houses with consistent exercise.</li>
          <li>A long-term family member who thrives with structure, affection, and training.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="cta-card">
        <h2>Ready to Meet Your Match?</h2>
        <p>Browse our available Dachshund puppies and contact us if you want help choosing the right temperament and size for your home.</p>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/available-puppies" class="btn-primary">View Available Puppies</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary">Ask Us a Question</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .breed-page {
    background: #F7FAF7;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-family, 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif);
  }

  .breed-container {
    max-width: 1020px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .intro-card,
  .info-card,
  .cta-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e8ddd4;
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(20, 53, 33, 0.08);
  }

  .intro-card h2,
  .info-card h2,
  .cta-card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    color: #143521;
    font-size: 1.9rem;
  }

  .intro-card p,
  .info-card p,
  .info-card li,
  .cta-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #595959;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .traits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .trait-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e8ddd4;
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1.35rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(20, 53, 33, 0.07);
  }

  .trait-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
    color: #1F5132;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .trait-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #5c5c5c;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    min-width: 700px;
  }

  th,
  td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ebdfd5;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.8rem 0.6rem;
    color: #4d4d4d;
  }

  th {
    color: #143521;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    background: #fcf7f1;
  }

  .info-card ul {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.45rem;
  }

  .cta-actions {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .btn-primary,
  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1F5132, #2E6B45);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    border: 1px solid #1F5132;
    color: #1F5132;
    background: #fff;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .breed-page {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    .traits-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .intro-card,
    .info-card,
    .cta-card {
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    .intro-card h2,
    .info-card h2,
    .cta-card h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
